    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/dr-cou1-cpb-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hemolysis-relevant QoI within acceptance thresholds across all five COU operating points. RH < 1.0 criterion satisfied at all operating points. Aleatory uncertainty sources (blood property variability, batch-to-batch erythrocyte fragility variation) are acknowledged in validation narratives; the assessment team notes that formal UQ artifacts are not uniformly linked to all validation results, which is considered acceptable at MRL 2 but should be addressed if the model risk level is elevated in future assessments. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
